==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[alterativus]]: compare with French [[altératif]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈɔl.tɚˌaɪ.tɪv/ or /ˈɔl.tɚ.ə.tɪv/

===Adjective===
# Causing [[alteration]]. Specifically: Gradually changing, or tending to change, a morbid state of the functions into one  of health. --Burton.


===Noun===
# A medicine or treatment which gradually induces a change, and  restores healthy functions without sensible evacuations.


